                <h2>FAQs</h2>
                <h3>How can I check the Delta flight status?</h3>
                <p>To check the Delta flight status, you need to visit Delta’s official website at delta.com. Once on the site, go to the “Flight Status” tab from the main menu. You can then track your flight by either searching by route or flight number.</p>
                <h3>What are the two ways to search for Delta flight status?</h3>
                <p>You can search for Delta flight status in two ways:</p>
                <p>- By Route: Enter the origin and destination cities or airport codes.</p>
                <p>- By Flight Number: Enter the specific flight number to track the status of that particular flight.</p>
                <h3>What information do I need to view Delta flight status?</h3>
                <p>To view the flight status, you need the following information:</p>
                <p>- The origin and destination cities or their airport codes.</p>
                <p>- The departure date and year of the flight.</p>
                <h3>What happens after I click on "View Flight Status"?</h3>
                <p>After you enter the required details and click on "View Flight Status," you will be able to see the live status of the Delta flight, including updates on departure times, delays, or cancellations.</p>
